Although  profuse (Fig.  3B)  the  suppression  of  atg8Δ  conidi-ation  was  lower  in  glucose  (about  64  x  102 conidia/cm2; Fig. 3A) when compared to that induced by sucrose; Glucose-6-phosphate caused  a  remarkable  suppression  of conidiation defects. However, exogenous Glucose-1-phosphate was unable to suppress the conidiation defects
